A clean, modern, and professional WordPress blog theme built for writers,
journalists, and content creators.

== Description ==

Evoke by Ayush is a fast, lightweight, and fully responsive blog theme with a
card-based post layout, elegant typography, full widget-area support, custom
logo support, sticky header navigation with mobile menu, and a polished
footer with copyright and support details baked in.

== Installation ==

1. In your WordPress admin dashboard, go to Appearance > Themes > Add New > Upload Theme.
2. Choose the evoke-by-ayush.zip file and click "Install Now".
3. Activate the theme.
4. Go to Appearance > Customize to set your site logo, colors (via CSS if desired), and footer copyright text.
5. Go to Appearance > Menus to assign your Primary Menu and Footer Menu.
6. Go to Appearance > Widgets to add widgets to the Main Sidebar, Footer Column 1, and Footer Column 2 areas.

== Frequently Asked Questions ==

= Does this theme support a custom logo? =
Yes. Go to Appearance > Customize > Site Identity to upload your logo.

= Does this theme support widgets? =
Yes. It registers a Main Sidebar and two Footer widget areas.

= Is this theme translation ready? =
Yes, all strings are wrapped for translation with the text domain "evoke-by-ayush".

